Bio: Born and raised on the track, we create the most advanced performance cars in the world.
Caption text:
This week McLaren Tech Club takes us to Denmark, to our friends at the LEGO HQ. The McLaren Senna GTR is a truly special car. Unique in its aerodynamic capabilities and utterly extreme in its performance, it is truly uncompromising in its approach to lap times. 

Translating something so extreme into LEGO Technicâ„¢ was no easy feat, taking all of @lego incredible design processes to produce the amazing LEGO Technicâ„¢ McLaren Senna GTR model.

So how did they do it? AureÌlien Rouge, Senior Designer at LEGO Technicâ„¢ explains the careful and considered design process behind the latest LEGO and McLaren Automotive collaboration.,The contours of the 720S are distinctly McLaren, yet the details are boldly different. Our designers took inspiration from the Great White Shark, a beautifully sleek yet brutally efficient hunting machine.,The 620R, pictured here in the seaside town of Little Hampton, is truly special. It not only looks like a race car, but it also handles, performs and feels like a race car too.,An innovation of the technology first seen in the McLaren P1â„¢ hypercar, the MonoCage II found in the 720S is a one-piece carbon fibre tub that now includes the roof. 

Extending over the engine bay, it includes wider door apertures that open into the roof.,Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park has hosted some of the worlds top performing athletes...and top performance is no stranger to the 720S. Itâ€™s blisteringly fast with phenomenal driver engagement. Fitting we enjoy the view.,In the GT, the wraparound glass cabin is designed for you to enjoy all-round views. Hour after hour. Mile after mile.,East Londonâ€™s trendsetting Shoreditch, is home to edgy and unique art. Acquainted with careful craftmanship the GT's profile is sleek but purposeful. This is a car that invites you to drive.,Our pioneering design gives the new GT a unique beauty and balance. Beneath the fluid surfaces, youâ€™ll find the innovative design and engineering thatâ€™s at the heart of every McLaren.,Providing some great driving roads for the McLaren GT to explore, we take a moment to stop in Bristol and admire the view, the GT is a masterpiece of tactile luxury and from the cabin... the view is always great.,Clifton Suspension Bridge, in Bristol, is one of the UK's most recognisable structures. Marking a turning point in the history of engineering; the bridge is iconic to the city. No wonder it has claimed a rightful place in #GTadventures.

Uppers are built of mostly white leather with the highlight being a colorful collage of graphics that reach from the forefoot to the heel and encompass everything from flowers to raindrops, a globe, and a hand-stenciled Trefoil logo. The shoe is available now via @atmos_japan for approximately $116 USD.â â €
Photo: atmosâ ,A new look at a @sacaiofficial x @jpgaultierofficial x @nike Vaporwaffle has surfaced online as we near Chitose Abeâ€™s debut for Jean Paul Gaultier couture. Sporting a familiar double-stacked midsole and doubled up Swooshes, the couture-focused shoe features an upper that boasts nylon, suede and leather, all split by Air Footscape Woven-like black or white stitching that runs across the midfoot and toebox. Catch it in action during Abeâ€™s first Gaultier runway.â â €
Photo: @sneakerjamz_new,@asics has unveiled a new GEL-QUANTUM 180 silhouette alongside the launch of its Spring/Summer 2021 â€œENGINEERED FOR EVERYDAYâ€ campaign. Tapping LA-based photographer @camhicks_ and London-based furniture designer @modularbymensah, the new shoe sees an aesthetic makeover on the upper featuring a mesh toe box with leather overlays similar to their running models. Look for it to come in two colorways on January 22 via the ASICS website and official stockists for approximately $170 USD each.â â €
Photo: ASICS,@jumpman23 is prepping a take on the Air Jordan 1 Low reminiscent of the @diamondsupplyco x @nike Dunk Low â€œTiffany.â€ Dubbed â€œTropical Twist,â€ this iteration carries the same two-tone look found on the 2005 release and features a teal leather base accented by black overlays and a matching nylon tongue. Branding comes in the form of gradient Swooshes, color-matched tongue tags, printed insoles, and tonal black embroidered Wings motifs at the rear. Stay tuned for official release details.â â €
Photo: Nike,@realcoleworld and @puma have officially announced the DREAMER 2 hoops shoe. Coming in an inaugural â€œJanuary 28â€ colorway, the model features abstractly shaped overlays with a blend of leather, suede and synthetic materials in a louder yellow hue. The bottom sole unit is coated with black, while hits of red make its way onto the pods on the outsoles. Expect it to be available via PUMAâ€™s NYC Flagship Store, website, and select stockists worldwide on January 28 for $135 USD.â â €

Kerri has a wealth of information and learnings to share as she seeks to grow and retain champion athlete status. Come get in on the mind of an athlete with Kerri Walsh Jennings.

Caption text: The Bodega x Nike Dunk High â€˜Friends & Familyâ€™ utilizes the same inspiration of Americana and old-world craftsmanship as the regular â€˜Legendâ€™ iteration, but arrives in a clean Sail and Birch colorway. Never released to the general public and given to friends and family of the Boston-based brand, consumers did have a shot at getting these if they purchased the â€˜Legendâ€™ colorway. Randomly inserting a pack of sports cards into 1 out of every 20 boxes, consumers who were lucky enough to find the cards could claim one of these F&F pairs. Available on the app and GOAT.com,The Social Status x Ultra 4D â€˜Renaissanceâ€™ blends a futuristic sneaker with historical inspiration. Utilizing colors and tones inspired from Renaissance art, specifically da Vinciâ€™s â€˜Mona Lisa,â€™ the Ultra 4D features bold colors across a Primeknit upper and suede cage. A 3-D printed midsole offers customized cushioning, while a gum rubber outsole and Social Status and adidas co-branding finish the look. Limited to only 3,020 pairs, shop them on the app and GOAT.com,The Nike womenâ€™s Lahar Low â€˜Wheatâ€™ delivers a contemporary interpretation of the Lahar Escape Boot from 1989, featuring a dark tan suede upper secured with rope laces and metal eyelets. An Air sole unit in the heel offers lightweight cushioning while an off-road traction pattern on the thick outsole provides maximum grip. Available on the app and GOAT.com,Paying homage to the original silhouette, the Nike Air Max 95 NDSTRKT â€˜Neonâ€™ updates the lifestyle runner with a durable build. Keeping a similar but updated design, reflective neon webbing straps integrate into a mesh upper reinforced with rubberized overlays and a molded TPU cage. The midsole maintains the look of the original Air Max 95, highlighted by visible Nike Air cushioning in the heel and forefoot. Available on the app and GOAT.com,Part of a festive capsule collection that included the New Balance 992, the â€˜Kithmas Collectionâ€™ saw Ronnie Fieg work on three colors of the classic running style. The â€˜Team Redâ€™ and â€˜Burgundy Reefâ€™ arrive with plush suede on the uppers, accented with mesh and leather detailing. A sculpted midsole features ABZORB technology for impact cushioning and dual branding finishes the look including KITH on the tongue and FIEG on the back heel. Available on the app and GOAT.com,A celebration of two high profile Nike athletes â€” LeBron James and Kylian MbappÃ© â€”results in unique iterations of the Nike Mercurial Superfly 7 and LeBron 18. The LeBron 18 â€˜The Chosen 2â€™ features iridescent detailing across a black Knitposite 2.0 upper and a translucent outsole. The athletesâ€™ inspiration can be seen throughout the shoe, including a basketball x football graphic and Chosen Two ambigram on the sockliners. Available on the app and GOAT.com,The Nike Dunk Low SP â€˜UNLVâ€™ revives one of the original colorways of the 1985 â€˜Be True to Your Schoolâ€™ series, but in a low cut format versus the original high-top. The upper utilizes the team colors of the University of Las Vegas, highlighted by a neutral grey leather base with University Red overlays and a contrasting white midsole. Available on the app and GOAT.com,Designed by the Guangzhou artist, the Jason Deng x Nike Dunk Low Pro SB â€˜Street Hawkerâ€™ pays homage to Chinese street food vendors and Chinese food culture at large. The uppers are covered in unique materials, colors, and Dengâ€™s watercolor graphics, with individual details representing six regional dishes from six Chinese cities. Theyâ€™re joined by additional cuisine-inspired flourishes, including a wood-grain Swoosh that nods to chopsticks, a blue-tinged sockliner representing porcelain bowls, and a coppery toe box standing in for boiling chili oil. â€˜Foodâ€™ is spelled out in embroidered Chinese calligraphy on the back heel tab. Available on the app and GOAT.com,Ronnie Fieg and ASICS embarked on an ambitious project to celebrate the 30th anniversary of the Gel Lyte 3. â€˜The Paletteâ€™ offers up thirty different iterations of the classic runner, crafted with premium suede in a tonal look. The colors were derived from KITH products throughout the brandâ€™s history, inspiring thirty unique pairs including this â€˜Dusty Mauveâ€™ colorway. Available on the app and GOAT.com,Part of a capsule collection with the Tokyo-based fashion label, the AMBUSH x Nike Dunk High â€˜Blackâ€™ applies a clean two-tone color scheme to the classic lifestyle silhouette. Inspired by Japanese bike, car and truck culture, an exaggerated Swoosh extends past the back of the shoe to convey a dynamic sense of movement while AMBUSH branding can be found on the TPU heel counter and on the tongue tag. Available on the app and GOAT.com

Enriching the proceedings with jolts of color, 'Dior and Peter Doig' camo print and refined embellishment, the ballet dancer @GuillaumeDiop, actor and musician @LukasIonesco and artist @KailandMorris caught yesterday's #DiorWinter21 digital show from @MrKimJones in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig wearing looks from the collection itself.
Â© @Thomas_Chene,With #DiorWinter21 from @MrKimJones in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig having been unveiled digitally yesterday, director @LadjLy and actors @ArnaudValois and @JLaheurte - wearing statement outerwear including a 'Dior and Peter Doig' print bomber jacket - were among the House friends from around the world discovering the new collection.
Â© @Thomas_Chene,Relive the finale of yesterdayâ€™s unveiling of #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones in collaboration with the artist @PeterDoig. The closing look, featuring a plush shearling coat with a long, officer-style jacket, distills the spirit of the collection which explores the codes of ceremonial costume in a couture-informed, contemporary take on timeless masculine elegance.,The expressive brushwork of collaborative artist @PeterDoig daubs the modesty-maintaining panels on the front of a pair of sheer shirts for #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones, illuminating the celebrated painter's process as well as his finished works.,The enigmatic allure of the paintings of collaborative artist @PeterDoig unfolds both boldly and hazily across a number of standout coats from #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones. These hypnotic 'Dior and Peter Doig' prints are derived from emblematic works by the internationally celebrated painter including 'Milky Way' (1990).,The air of masculine majesty conveyed by ceremonial garb is explored and modernized for #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones in collaboration with the artist @PeterDoig. The precision tailoring of officer jackets with their piping, braid and decorative buttons is mixed, in an inventive use of #DiorSavoirFaire, with embroideries possessing a more couture sensibility and tamed with the addition of colorful sportswear pieces, honoring history and heritage in a resolutely contemporary way.,See the show set from the recently-revealed #DiorWinter21 collection in which the collaboration between @MrKimJones and the artist @PeterDoig extended to an installation devised by the latter with blue skies and stacked sound systems that reference those in such paintings of his as 'Speaker/Girl' (2015). 
Â© Photo: @AdrienDirand,Knitwear provides a metaphorical canvas for animalistic imagery in the #DiorWinter21 collection by @MrKimJones in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig. The latter specially conceived two motifs - one that's a likeness of Monsieur Dior's beloved dog, Bobby, and the other a lion that references the artist's own output - both rendered with a blurred effect that mimics the painter's style, further alluded to in an evocation of brushstrokes on another sweater.,Sample some of the highlights of the just-unveiled #DiorWinter21 collection by @MrKimJones created in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig. Channeling the latterâ€™s oeuvre, whether indirectly through his color palette or directly through motifs drawn from his paintings, the collection draws inspiration from the timeless masculine elegance of ceremonial costume as viewed through a contemporary prism rooted in #DiorSavoirFaire.,Whether as layered looks in lustrous â€˜Dior and Peter Doigâ€™ camo prints or abstracted cashmere knits, the timeless military motif was reinterpreted in hues ranging from dusky to eye-popping in the just-ended showing of #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones in a nod to the palette associated with the collectionâ€™s collaborative artist @PeterDoig.

A galaxy far, far away...50 million light-years from Earth, in the constellation of Virgo, the "lost galaxy" NGC 4535 shines, with its delicate swirls of newborn stars, burning furiously against their cool, blue ancestors.Despite the incredible quality of this image, taken from the NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope, NGC 4535 has a hazy, somewhat ghostly, appearance when viewed from a smaller telescope - inspiring its nickname, the â€œLost Galaxyâ€.Credit: ESA/Hubble & NASA, J. Lee and the PHANGS-HST Team#NASA #Universe #Galaxy #Stars #Dreamy #Hubble #Virgo,Early evening sunlight dances down the valleys to warm the icy terrain.This natural-color Landsat 8 data was draped over a global digital elevation model of Greenland to create this unique view. The area lies a bit northeast of GunnbjÃ¸rn Fjeld, the tallest mountain in the country. The region is dotted with nunataksâ€”rocky peaks that stick through glaciers and ice sheetsâ€”in the Watkins Range, Greenlandâ€™s tallest mountain range.Credit: NASA#Nasa #Greenland #MountainRange #Shadows #Light,ğŸ”µFrom Florida to Pluto to the Kuiper Belt and beyond!Exactly 15 years ago today, an uncrewed NASA spacecraft by the name of New Horizons blasted off on a 3 billion-mile journey to Pluto from Cape Canaveral Air Force Station by an @ULALaunch Atlas rocket at a speed of about 36,400Â mph (16.26Â km/s). It was the fastest human-made object EVER launched from Earth.By launching in 2006, New Horizons was able to take advantage of an assist from Jupiter. The Pluto probe approached a rendezvous with Jupiter and used the giant planet as a gravity-based slingshot. The five-month flyby induced a colossal burst of speed, accelerating the spacecraft by 9000 mph up to 52,000 mph. At that wild speed, you could soar from Los Angeles to New York in less than 4 minutes!After passing through the Pluto system in 2015, the spacecraft retargeted itself for an encounter with a Kuiper Belt Object (KBO) called Arrokoth, a Native American term meaning â€œskyâ€ in the Powhatan/Agonquian language. While there, the spacecraft gathered data that researchers believe could contribute to our understanding of the origin of life on Earth.Credit: ğŸ”µNASAğŸ”µNASA/JHUAPL/SwRIğŸ”µNASA/Johns Hopkins University Applied Physics Laboratory/Southwest Research Institute/Roman Tkachenko#NASA #Pluto #PlutoFlyBy #Space #Galaxy #Universe #Exploration,"Darkness cannot drive out darkness, only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out hate, only love can do that." â€” Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.â£

#MLKDay #NASA #Space #Atlanta #CityLights #Love,How blue-tiful! ğŸ¤©ğŸŒŒNear the outskirts of the Small Magellanic Cloud, a satellite galaxy about 200 thousand light-years away, lies this 5 million year young and dazzling star cluster known as NGC 602. Inside the star cluster, bright, blue, newly formed stars are blowing a cavity in this nebula, sculpting the inner edge of its outer portions, slowly eroding it away and eating into the material beyond. Star formation started at the center of the cluster and propagated outward, with the youngest stars still forming today along the dust ridges.Fun fact: Did you know that the color of a star is directly linked to its surface temperature? The hotter the star, the shorter the wavelength of light it will emit. The hottest of stars are blue or blue-white and the cooler ones are red or red-brown. What color star would you be?Credit: NASA#NASA #Stars #Universe #Galaxy #BlueStars #Astronomy #FunFacts,Get in loser, we're going stargazing ğŸŒŒMagnetic fields in Messier 82, or the Cigar galaxy, are shown here as lines over a visible light and infrared composite image of the galaxy from the @NASAHubble & the Spitzer Space Telescope. The galaxy located in the constellation Ursa Major is remarkable. Stellar winds streaming from hot new stars form a galactic super wind that blasts out plumes of hot gas (red) and a huge halo of smoky dust (yellow/orange) perpendicular to the narrow galaxy (white). Researchers used the Stratospheric Observatory for Infrared Astronomy (@sofiatelescope) magnetic field data and tools that have been used extensively to study the physics around the Sun to extrapolate the magnetic fieldâ€™s strength 20,000 lights-years around the galaxy. The highways appear to extend indefinitely into intergalactic space, like the Sunâ€™s solar wind, and may help explain how the gas and dust have traveled so far away from the galaxy. Credits: NASA, SOFIA, L. Proudfit; NASA, ESA, Hubble Heritage Team; NASA, JPL-Caltech, C. Engelbracht#NASA #M82 #Galaxy #Universe #Constellation #CigarGalaxy #UrsaMajor #SpaceHighway,In squad we trust ğŸš€Upside down or right side up? The seven-member Expedition 64 crew takes a moment to pose for a quick portrait inside the @ISSâ€™ Kibo laboratory module from @jaxajp (Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency). Expedition 64 began in back in October 2020 with focused research investigations on biology, Earth science, human research, and more to provide the foundation for continuing human spaceflight beyond low-Earth orbit to the Moon and Mars!In the bottom row:NASA astronaut Kate Rubins@roscosmosofficial cosmonautsâ­ Sergey Ryzhikovâ­ Sergey Kud-SverchkovIn the top row:â­ @jaxajp astronaut @astro.soichi@NASAAstronautsâ­ Michael Hopkinsâ­ @AstroVicGloverâ­ Shannon WalkerGlover and Hopkins are wearing white uniforms that commemorate the NASA human spaceflight programs Mercury, Gemini, Apollo, Apollo-Soyuz, Space Shuttle, Shuttle-Mir, International Space Station and Commercial Crew.Credit: NASA#NASA #SquadGoals #Astronauts #Apollo #Expedition64 #Family #CommercialCrew #Science #STEM #Skywalkers,ğŸ¤¯ Discovery alert: We donâ€™t know of many planets quite like this!Thanks to data from our @NASAGoddard TESS mission, a planet existing around THREE stars has been confirmed, after a hefty hunt that spanned about 11 years! It all started shortly after NASA's Kepler mission began operations in 2009, when it identified what was thought to be a planet about the size of Neptune later known as KOI-5Ab. The planet which was the second new planet candidate to be found by the mission, was ultimately forgotten as Kepler racked up planet discoveries. Now, the chief scientist of NASAâ€™s Exoplanet Science Institute says he has â€œresurrected KOI-5Ab from the dead!" and we are so glad he did. Planet KOI-5Ab (shown here transiting across the face of a sun-like star), is located 1,800 light-years away in the Cygnus constellation. It is about one half the mass of Saturn & orbits a star (star A) with a relatively close companion (star B). Star A and star B orbit each other every 30 years. A third gravitationally bound star (star C) orbits stars A and B every 400 years.Illustration Credits: Caltech/R. Hurt (Infrared Processing and Analysis Center, or IPAC)#NASA #Galaxy #Universe #NewWorld #TripleStarSystem #NewDiscovery #LookUp #Space,Itâ€™s more than a feeling ğŸµMuch like the delicate filamentsÂ of a spider's web, the glowing lights of the city of Boston seemingly spread from a central point in this image taken by the crew of the @ISS as it orbited 263 miles above Earth's surface. What city would you want to look at if you were fluttering about in space on a Friday in January?Credit: NASA#NASA #Earth #Views #Galaxy #Universe #Boston #Massachusetts,Bon Voyage, #Cygnus! ğŸ¦¾Yesterday, about three months after delivering nearly 8,000 pounds (3,628 kilograms) of scientific experiments, supplies, commercial products, hardware, and more to the @ISS, @NorthropGrummanâ€™s uncrewed Cygnus cargo spacecraft departed the orbiting lab. Flight controllers on the ground sent commands to use the @CanadianSpaceAgency's Canadarm2 robotic arm to robotically detach Cygnus from the Earth-facing port of the unity module and maneuver it into place. Before the craft took off, the crew packed Cygnus with the Saffire V investigation & the SharkSat hosted payload to be conducted during an extended mission in orbit.  It'll complete a series of milestones to move away safely & remain in orbit until Jan. 26, for an extended mission with science experiments.Photo Credit: NASA#NASA #NorthropGrumman #USA #Canada #Robotics #Earth #ISS #CanadArm2

#alpine #alpinea110 #alpinea110s #renaultalpine #renaultalpinea110 #drift #drifting #driftcar  #motorsport #topgear #stigdrifts #thestig,More pics of Singer's awesome All-terrain Competition Study (ACS) - a co-developed project between Singer and British company Tuthill Porsche. 

Built at the request of a client who wanted an air-cooled 911 that could cope with the worldâ€™s most extreme off-road races, it pays homage to a golden era of Porsche rallying in the 1980s and to cars like the 959 Safari. 

It has four-wheel drive, a turbocharged flat-six, carbon panels, trick suspension and a stripped out interior, but still retains the outrageous attention to detail of all Singerâ€™s creations. 

Here it is in action. Get the full story at TopGear.com. Link in bio.

#topgear #singer #acs #porsche #dakar #rally #motorsport #carsofinstagram #carsofinsta,Ever wondered what goes on at the Top Gear test track when the show's not being filmed? Well it's this. Constant, non-stop THIS. Yep, Stig's got his hands on the latest 720bhp Merc-AMG Black Series and wants to bonfire some tyres. Enjoy...

#mercedes #mercedesamg #mercedesamggt #amggt #topgear #topgearmagazine #thestig,This is a serious car, for serious driving. We know this because no other production car has ever hammered around the Nordschleife faster than the AMG GT Black Series.

This is a consummate performer on the track. A road car that looks, acts and feels more like a GT3 racer than any other. If you want a car to fill you with confidence and make you feel every inch the hardcore racer, this new Black Series does it.

AMGs are traditionally engine-dominated, and this one has 150bhp more than the next model down the range. But by switching to a flat-plane crankshaft, the 4.0 twin-turbo V8 can now rev much higher and that allows the torque to be introduced more gently and sustained for longer. So it's got better traction. Unless...

Insert The Stig into the new Black Series and this most binary of not-quite-humans will revert to either his zero or one setting: flat-out or flat-out with lots of smoke. Clearly, The Stig believes a Black Series should be for one thing only. And it does do that one thing spectacularly well. Provided you are, in fact, The Stig. The rest of us mere mortals are going to find the Black Series somewhat harder to boss around...

#rolls #rollsroyce #TopGear #Ghost #RollsRoyceGhost #luxury #luxurycars #carsofinstagram #carsofinsta,The last 12 months have seen some cracking new additions and a few mid-life alterations to the hot hatch game. #toyotagryaris #gryaris #honda #CivicTypeR #TypeR #AMG #FiestaST #ford #hyundai #hyundaii30n #audi #S3,Meet the 1980s bike that fits into a tiny wee hot hatch.

The Motocompo is the smallest scooter Honda ever made. Which is no accident, because what youâ€™re looking at is a bike designed specifically to fold up and squeeze into the boot of a car.

The car it was designed as an accessory to was also a tiddler, the City hatchback which is essentially an ancestor of todayâ€™s Jazz. Thus the â€˜Compo had to be really small, and folded up, itâ€™s 118cm by 54cm and sits held in place by a couple of simple harnesses in the back of the City II Turbo as snugly as a plastic toy inside a Kinder Egg.

Production lasted just two years, with sales between 1981 and â€™83 just tipping over 50,000. But while itâ€™s undeniably a cute solution to urban gridlock, the process of parking up your car and unfurling the bike it sheathes is far from elegant. The Motocompo may be little bigger than a holiday suitcase, but with a 49cc two-stroke and a fuel tank aboard, itâ€™s significantly chunkier at about 45 kilos...

#TopGear #AutomotivePhotography #Honda #Motocompo #HondaMotocompo #Retrobikes #RetroScooters,Hereâ€™s a question - would you book a two week holiday off work, fly half way around the world with your wife and two kids in tow, just to see a Vauxhall?

Thought not. But thatâ€™s exactly what an Aussie family did at the Goodwood Festival of Speed, and youâ€™re looking at the reason for that mammoth trip right here. She (and yes, â€˜sheâ€™ is definitely the correct term) is called Baby Bertha.

Bertha hails from the mid-70s, a time when the wildly popular British club racing scene (think British Touring Cars at the height of their late 90s pomp), featured drivers with mutton chop sideburns and cars with cartoonish proportions. With a 0-100mph time of 7.8 seconds, she was 6.2 seconds faster than a contemporary Lamborghini Countach. Bertha was designed for one thing only: to win the Super Saloon championship.

Two seasons later and sheâ€™d won it twice on the bounce: box very much ticked. In her first year in 1975, she won 20 of the 24 races she entered. The following year it was 10 from 13, with two retirements and a second. That season also happened to include six lap records, all bar one of them with an average speed of over 100mph.

Worth travelling the world for? Head over to TopGear.com to find out why this legendary racer still pulls in the crowds. Link in bio.

ğŸŒŠ @therealshannonlee flows with @kerrileewalsh.  Kerri Lee Walsh Jennings is the most decorated Olympic beach volleyball player of all time, with 3 gold medals and one bronze. She is the beach volleyball career leader in both victories and winnings and at age 41 is making her run up to another Olympics in Tokyo this summer and aiming for a fourth gold medal.  Kerri is married to beach volleyball player Casey Jennings and together they have three children. In fact, she competed while pregnant in the Olympics twice! Kerri and Casey launched their company @p1440 in 2018, a digital sports platform created to inspire everyone to live 1440 minutes of every day with purpose.

Kerri is an ardent Bruce Lee fan as you will come to see when you listen to this episode. With Kerri, her energy leaps out at you. She is a fast paced, energetic woman who channels Bruce Lee (and two other icons) on the court. [And youâ€™ll want to find out which other 2 icons because it was pretty fascinating to me.] Kerri admits her fallibility and knows she is still learning and growing everyday as she continues to train and shoot for Olympic gold! She is a driven, passionate woman who is dedicated to her sport, her family and her faith. She is truly a go-getter who finds grounding in gratitude.  Kerri has a wealth of information and learnings to share as she seeks to grow and retain champion athlete status. Come get in on the mind of an athlete with Kerri Walsh Jennings.

Bio: "Women, with their intuitive instinct, understood that I dreamed not only of making them more beautiful, but happier too." Christian Dior
Caption text:
Enriching the proceedings with jolts of color, 'Dior and Peter Doig' camo print and refined embellishment, the ballet dancer @GuillaumeDiop, actor and musician @LukasIonesco and artist @KailandMorris caught yesterday's #DiorWinter21 digital show from @MrKimJones in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig wearing looks from the collection itself.
Â© @Thomas_Chene,With #DiorWinter21 from @MrKimJones in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig having been unveiled digitally yesterday, director @LadjLy and actors @ArnaudValois and @JLaheurte - wearing statement outerwear including a 'Dior and Peter Doig' print bomber jacket - were among the House friends from around the world discovering the new collection.
Â© @Thomas_Chene,Relive the finale of yesterdayâ€™s unveiling of #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones in collaboration with the artist @PeterDoig. The closing look, featuring a plush shearling coat with a long, officer-style jacket, distills the spirit of the collection which explores the codes of ceremonial costume in a couture-informed, contemporary take on timeless masculine elegance.,The expressive brushwork of collaborative artist @PeterDoig daubs the modesty-maintaining panels on the front of a pair of sheer shirts for #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones, illuminating the celebrated painter's process as well as his finished works.,The enigmatic allure of the paintings of collaborative artist @PeterDoig unfolds both boldly and hazily across a number of standout coats from #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones. These hypnotic 'Dior and Peter Doig' prints are derived from emblematic works by the internationally celebrated painter including 'Milky Way' (1990).,The air of masculine majesty conveyed by ceremonial garb is explored and modernized for #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones in collaboration with the artist @PeterDoig. The precision tailoring of officer jackets with their piping, braid and decorative buttons is mixed, in an inventive use of #DiorSavoirFaire, with embroideries possessing a more couture sensibility and tamed with the addition of colorful sportswear pieces, honoring history and heritage in a resolutely contemporary way.,See the show set from the recently-revealed #DiorWinter21 collection in which the collaboration between @MrKimJones and the artist @PeterDoig extended to an installation devised by the latter with blue skies and stacked sound systems that reference those in such paintings of his as 'Speaker/Girl' (2015). 
Â© Photo: @AdrienDirand,Knitwear provides a metaphorical canvas for animalistic imagery in the #DiorWinter21 collection by @MrKimJones in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig. The latter specially conceived two motifs - one that's a likeness of Monsieur Dior's beloved dog, Bobby, and the other a lion that references the artist's own output - both rendered with a blurred effect that mimics the painter's style, further alluded to in an evocation of brushstrokes on another sweater.,Sample some of the highlights of the just-unveiled #DiorWinter21 collection by @MrKimJones created in collaboration with artist @PeterDoig. Channeling the latterâ€™s oeuvre, whether indirectly through his color palette or directly through motifs drawn from his paintings, the collection draws inspiration from the timeless masculine elegance of ceremonial costume as viewed through a contemporary prism rooted in #DiorSavoirFaire.,Whether as layered looks in lustrous â€˜Dior and Peter Doigâ€™ camo prints or abstracted cashmere knits, the timeless military motif was reinterpreted in hues ranging from dusky to eye-popping in the just-ended showing of #DiorWinter21 by @MrKimJones in a nod to the palette associated with the collectionâ€™s collaborative artist @PeterDoig.

Bio: Experience the world through the eyes of National Geographic photographers.
Caption text:
Video by @joelsartore / A Learâ€™s macaw eyes the camera during a Photo Ark shoot @loroparque. Named after Edward Lear, an artist who was famous for painting macaws during the mid-19th century, this is one of the most mysterious birds on Earth. For more than a hundred years, nobody knew where Learâ€™s macaws lived in the wild. The mystery was solved in 1978 with the bird being re-discovered in the Bahia state of northeast Brazil. At the time, only 60 birds remained, but thanks to the work of many environmental groups and government agencies, there are more than a thousand worldwide today.  #macaw #endangered #PhotoArk #savetogether,Photo by @laurakmorton / Commercial fishing vessels are seen docked along the waterfront in San Francisco, Californiaâ€™s Fishermanâ€™s Wharf neighborhood. While the neighborhood is consistently ranked the cityâ€™s number one visitor destination, behind the tourist-focused businesses an essential fishing industry still operates there. Millions of pounds of seafood come through the wharf annually, and the wharf's Pier 45 houses the West Coast's largest concentration of commercial fish processors and distributors. Supported by @InsideNatGeoâ€™s Emergency Fund for Journalists I am currently working on a project on the Fishermanâ€™s Wharf neighborhood to document the economic issues created by the COVID-19 pandemic, which are affecting communities relying on tourism around the globe. For more from this story and photographs of people, places, and culture follow along @laurakmorton.,Photo by @erintrieb / A scene of skiers on Park City Mountain, Utah. Despite nationwide closures and travel bans throughout the U.S., most states' ski resorts remain open for the season, with social distancing and face-covering requirements in place. For more stories from around the world follow @erintrieb.,Photo by @celestesloman / This is a virtual portrait of Christiana Neazer, from Rialto, California, who lost her husband, Michael Neazer, to COVID-19. The 30-year-old nursing school student is pregnant with their child, due on March 15, which would have been the couple's sixth wedding anniversary.

In December and January I documented six families that lost relatives to the COVID-19 pandemic. Writer Katie Sanders explores what it means to say goodbye from a distance, whether that is a hazmat suit, via Zoom, or through text message. For this project I was also documenting at a distance, creating virtual portraits from my studio in Brooklyn.

Since it was too risky to travel and take these portraits in person, we decided to create virtual portraits from my Brooklyn studio. This approach seemed fitting because the story focuses on distance, separation, and communication through devices, so I created a still-life setup with my iPad surrounded by white flowers, to commemorate those lost. I FaceTimed with each of the families and directed them in the frame while I took photographs of the setup.

Check out Nat Geo's link in bio for more on this story.,Photos by Michael Yamashita @yamashitaphoto / The Great Wall meets water in the Panjiakou reservoir. The reservoir was created after the Luan River was dammed in the late 1970s, submerging sections of the wall and turning farmers into fishermen. In times of drought, more wall is exposed as the lake level drops. Fishermen cast their nets over the submerged sections as the wall acts like an artificial reef attracting the fish stocked in its waters. The Panjiakou reservoir supplies water to the Tianjin Province. #panjiakou #panjiakoureservoir #greatwall #greatwallofchina #reservoir,Photo by @paulnicklen / As winter turns to spring in Antarctica's Ross Sea, baby penguins poke tiny beaks through delicate eggshells and begin exploring their vast new polar surroundings. Meanwhile, four-foot-tall, 80-pound parents consider the precious fruit of their months-long labor with great curiosity. I am awestruck by the unfaltering dedication and commitment emperor penguins demonstrate for their youngâ€”they are fascinated by their chicks and marvel at every moment. Follow me @paulnicklen to see how love belongs to every species. #penguin #emperorpenguin #rosssea #antarctica #fascination,Photo by LujaÌn Agusti @lujanag / Eagle Pass, Texas, United States. Portrait of Maverick County Sheriff Tom Schmerber, who spoke out against Trump's anti-immigrant measures and declares, "I can see why people are running away from persecution. Maybe they are just looking for a better life." Follow me at @lujanag to learn more about this and other stories.

Check out Nat Geo's link in bio for more on this story.,Photo by @simonnorfolkstudio / Photographed on my second assignment for National Geographic magazine, twelve years ago, Naqsh-e Rustam is the acropolis of the great Persian kings of the 5th and 4th century BCE, with the high tombs of Darius II, Ataxerxes I, and Xerxes I. The site is near the ruined city of Persepolis in western Iran. In the foreground is the mysterious Kaâ€™be-ye Zartosht, which has been thought to be either a tomb, a sacred library, or possibly a chamber for the keeping of holy fire. Follow me @simonnorfolkstudio for updates, outtakes, unpublished, and archive material. #archaeology #iran #Persia #Persianempire #Achaemenidempire,Photo by @nicholesobecki / At the Burao camp for internally displaced persons, a woman watches a swarm of locusts darken the sky. Erratic climate conditions that cause severe droughts across the Horn of Africa in some years yield extreme rainfall in othersâ€”the trigger, in 2019, for the worst outbreak of desert locusts Somalia has seen in decades. The locusts can devour a field of crops in hours. As National Geographic and @everydayeverywhere explore how difficult, fraught conditions around the world are pushing women from their homes, I returned to Somaliland and Kenya, where the climate crisis is a major driver. To see more of my work on humanityâ€™s connection to the natural world, please follow @nicholesobecki.

Check out Nat Geo's link in bio for more on this story.,Photo by Daniella Zalcman @dzalcman / If you tuned into the U.S. presidential Inauguration yesterday, you would have heard Amanda Gorman read "The Hill We Climb," at 22 the youngest inaugural poet in American history. This portrait is from 2017, when she was named the first ever National Youth Poet Laureate. "Somehow weâ€™ve weathered and witnessed a nation that isnâ€™t broken, but simply unfinished," her poem reads. "We, the successors of a country and a time, where a skinny black girl descended from slaves and raised by a single mother can dream of becoming president only to find herself reciting for one."

Kazim-Richards only spent one season at Brighton, who finished bottom of the Championship. After relegation he went to Premier League Sheffield United, and when they went down, he started his globetrotting tour. After one season Kazim-Richards was on the move again, rocking up at Feyenoord. Here he really hit form there, netting 13 times in the 2014/15 season.
